Aim:To manually review a login wedule for insecure practices and prepare secure code fixes.

Theory:

Plain-text password's:
     stared as is; database compromise teaks all credentials.

S&l Injection:
      User input concatenated into sat queries, attackers bypass authentication or extract dota

Mixing Input Validation:
      No checks on empty/special characters; loade te injection and Unexpected behaviour

Hardcoded Credenthals:
      Database passwords inside source code; exposed if files are readable

No-Password Hashing:
      Raw Passwords compromised; violates confidentiality.

No-Session Management
      Login success doesn't create a session; user not truly logged in

Methodology:

1.Setup
      Install Apache, MySaL, PHP on Parrot OS; Create/var/www/html/login-lab.

2. Build Vulnerable login
      Index html from login.php with hardcoded DB credentials.

3. Review Code
      Identify flaws: 5al injection, missing validation, no sessions etc.

4.Exploit
      Use payload 'OR '1'-- to bypass login; query DB to see plantert password

5. Secure Implementation
      Replace with prepared statements; external configurations, impot validation and session start.

6. Test Secure Version
      Valid login works; injection fails; Passwords hashed in DB.

7. Document
      List vulnerabilities; severity and fixes.

Future Scope:
      Add MFA and rate-Limiting to evolve this lab into a production-ready authentication system for real world web application.
